The paper deals with cooperative pathfinding, which involves multiple agents working together to find paths without conflicts. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) as it involves planning and control of multiple agents. The paper also proposes an algorithm that uses potential fields, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and control systems (cs.SY) as it involves coordinating the actions of multiple agents. Finally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to improve the algorithm, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
